Login to the system with user ccf128

Following process will indicate the installation steps for both R and RStudio

step 1 : INSTALL R
open terminal ctrl + alt + T

sudo apt-get update 
sudo apt-get install r-base

press R command on terminal window, you'll get R prompt

R

step 2 : INSTALL RStudio

open browser window and go to following path
https://download1.rstudio.org/rstudio-0.99.902-i386.deb

This will download RStudio Debian package
go to Downloads directory and right click on this file
open with Ubuntu Software Center

It will open USC, click on install, give the password
After few minutes, RStudio will be installed.

You can access it under Applications->Programming->RStudio OR start->RStudio
